<p class="">I will give way to the hon. Gentleman, who is always courteous to me, in a moment, if I may finish my argument, but I have warned the House that my speech will be long anyway, and it will inevitably be longer still if I am unable to speak more than a few sentences without interruption.<p></p> The point I was making was that, regarding this excessive functional division of responsibility, however understandable it may have been in the early days, when there was need to get standardisation and some sort of approach to the principle of central responsibility, I think the time for that has passed. Now I wish to come to a further and even more important point than the one with which I was dealing.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
