<p class="">There is a plan now before the Minister from the British Transport Commission suggesting the integration of certain collections and deliveries between rail and road. However, now this Government is in power those proposals, which were the first step towards the integration of which the hon. Gentleman speaks, will not be followed through. They have come forward <span id="1452" class="column-number" data-column-number="1452"></span> after four years because much of that time has been taken in getting the service started.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
